1 A BILL for an Act to amend and reenact sections 39-04-11, 39-04-12, 39-04-37, and 39-04-56 of
2 the North Dakota Century Code, relating to display of temporary registration permits; and to
3 provide a penalty.
4 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATIVE ASSEMBLY OF NORTH DAKOTA:
5 SECTION 1. AMENDMENT. Section 39-04-11 of the North Dakota Century Code is
6 amended and reenacted as follows:
7 39-04-11. Display of number plates and tabs - Temporary registration.
8 Unless otherwise provided by law, an individual may not operate a vehicle on a public
9 highway of this state unless the vehicle has a distinctive number assigned to the vehicle by the
10 department, and two number plates, bearing the distinctive number conspicuously displayed,
11 horizontally and in an upright position, one on the front and one on the rear of the vehicle, each
12 securely fastened, except number plates assigned to a housetrailer must be attached to the
13 rear of the housetrailer. An individual may operate a motor vehicle on a public highway of this
14 state with a valid temporary registration permit. A temporary registration permit obtained from
15 the department of transportation or an authorized car dealership must be displayed on the lower
16 left of the rear window, free of any obstructions, and clearly visible to the rear. Number plates
17 assigned to a motorcycle or trailer must be attached to the rear of the motorcycle or trailer and
18 may be displayed vertically. When only one number plate is furnished for an apportioned vehicle
19 registered under the international registration plan as authorized in section 39-19-04, truck
20 tractor, or semitrailer, the plate must be attached to the front of the apportioned vehicle or truck
21 tractor and the rear of the semitrailer. The bottom of each number plate must be at a height of
22 not less than twelve inches [30.48 centimeters] above the level surface upon which the vehicle
23 stands. Each plate must be mounted in a visible manner that clearly displays the distinctive
24 number assigned to the vehicle and the name of the state on the plate. As far as is reasonably
